
Installing on linux (Ubuntu 19.10)
=================================

== already installed
mpv
libmpv-dev
python3-numpy

== install (with apt-get,  aptitude)
git
python3
  matplotlib
  scipy
  pyqt5
  pyqt5.quick
  pip3
  qt5-default
  qtdeclarative5-dev
  qml-module-qtquick-layout
                    -dialogs
		    -controls2
	(currently version 2.12)
  qml-module-qt-labs-settings
  qml-module-qt-labs-folderlistmodel

== with pip3
  pylatex

== optionally (via apt-get) to make reports in pdf
texlive
texlive-latex-extra
  evt. zie https://www.latex-project.org/get
  
== optionally for video
python-mpv
   - from: https://github.com/jaseg/python-mpv
   - install via pip3

== the versions should be fairly resent, otherwise there are warnings or errors.
- Basic testing
    - Command:  python tstqtquick.py
       - yields a yellow window
    - Command:  pythong tstmatplotlib.py
       - a simple plot

== hack matplotlib met diff_matplotlib
  Change the 3 lines in the file described in the patch-file.
  Without this there are a lot of (harmless) errors on exiting the program.  




